The Range Rover driver who was captured on video driving in the water at a Richards Bay beach, northern KwaZulu-Natal is remanded in custody until February 10. ALSO READ | WATCH | Dangerous KZN beach driver sought by authorities The 31-year-old Thulani Cele appeared at the Richards Bay Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday on charges related to driving his car in a coastal area without permission in terms of the Environmental Management Act. KwaZulu-Natal spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala, said police officers received a complaint of a video that was circulating on social media of Cele driving through Bay Hall Coastal Zone in Richards bay. “An investigation to locate the suspect led police to acquiring information of the owner of the vehicle. On January 4, he was brought to Richards Bay SAPS where he was arrested and charged,” said Gwala. Videos of Cele trended on social media on New Year’s Day where he was seen driving his car in the water where people swimming. His passengers had their head out through the car’s sunroof. Another video showed the car stuck in the water after it was swallowed by the tide.